A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a chaotic mail sorting room, with dozens of colorful envelopes and letters flying through the air in swirling patterns, some landing in neat wooden pigeonholes while others get redirected and shuffled between different compartments. A mechanical sorting machine with brass gears and levers sits at the center, its conveyor belts sending mail in unexpected directions. The color palette features warm mustard yellows, burnt oranges, and teal blues typical of mid-century design. Envelopes cast dramatic shadows against cream-colored walls, creating a sense of organized confusion and perpetual motion.
